laboratory_examinations.findings: Normal lung fields with no signs of pneumonia. Subtle irregularities involving the bilateral inferior ribs suggestive of inferior rib notching.

Revealed large collateral vessels in the chest wall, tortuously dilated internal mammary arteries, posterior and anterior intercostal arteries, and large paravertebral and parascapular collateral vessels. A complete discontinuity between the aortic arch and descending thoracic aorta noted with a 1.5 cm gap. 3D reconstruction showed distinct outline of aortic interruption.
